        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="855" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <head>Señor <persName type="from">Banuelos</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Perry</persName>
                </head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State, Bureau of Political Affairs</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-09">May 9, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Most Excellent Sir</hi>: The president of the council
                        of ministers, on the 5th instant, directed this department as follows:</p>
                <p>By her Majesty’s orders, and for the instruction of the department under your
                        charge, I transmit to your excellency copies of the resolutions passed by
                        the Senate and House of Representatives, sympathizing with the United
                        States, and deploring the abominable crime committed upon the person of your
                        worthy President, Mr. Abraham Lincoln. Communicated by royal order, through
                        the minister of state, I transmit them to you, with the said copies, that
                        you may send them to your government.</p>
                <p>God grant you many years.</p>
                <closer>Under Secretary <signed>MIGUEL BANUELOS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
